@Bill Famous quote: "Die ganzen Zahlen hat der liebe Gott gemacht, alles andere ist Menschenwerk."---Leopold Kronecker

“God created the integers, and the rest is the work of man.”

In mathematics, the real numbers (which we depict as an line) is a proper subset of the complex numbers (which we depict as a plane). In the latter depiction, the points on the x-axis are the real numbers, and all other points in the xy-plane are non-real complex numbers. The imaginary number 𝘪 corresponds to the point (x,y) = (0,1) in this model.

@Xword Junkie 
Great quote!
In my mind, even the positive integers are imaginary abstractions: I can hold three apples, but can I hold a three? All the other numbers spread out from there, in increasing dimensions of non-reality.

